<br>
I just want to talk about HGs (Hill Giants) in RM, now I'm pretty sure EVERYMOB that roams on the HG hill is a PH for a HG (I used to note one spawn path and point near the Lizzie camp, and it could be either one of lizard, skelly, cyclops or a HG)<br>
<br>
Anyway, everytime I arrive at RM, I always see a minimum of 5-10 PH, lizardmen basilisk etc on top of the hill. And people were always complaining about lack of HG at one point or another. I ALWAYS shout for people to kill more PH. It's kinda weird when people say the place is empty when I can see so many non-HG up there. <br>
<br>
Granted, I'm running a 52 monk, so most PH is a 3 sec fight for me. But surely for druids, can't they spare like 1 DD to kill a basilisk or a lizardmen, let's say every 3-4 Hill Giants? I'm not asking people to kill cyclops or even giant skeletons (I DO kill cyclops as well)<br>
<br>
I did the numbers last night, killed 312 PH (non HG) and killed 62 Hill Giants. <br>
<br>
I'm not complaining about me not getting enough HG (I had to train out a few times, too many HG for me). I AM complaining about people's unwillingness to spend that extra bit of mana or time to kill a puny little lizardmen PH.<br>
<br>
